 TreeHouse Foods, Inc. Names Chris Sliva to New Post of Chief Operating Officer for Bay Valley Foods 
         










    










 






 











 









TreeHouse Foods, Inc. Names Chris Sliva to New Post of Chief Operating Officer for Bay Valley Foods Unit

Jul 23, 2012, 16:00 ET
		  		  					
						 from   TreeHouse Foods, Inc. 











 
















































 

 




















 


OAK BROOK, Ill., July 23, 2012 /PRNewswire/ -- TreeHouse Foods, Inc. (NYSE:   THS) announced today a new alignment of its executive leadership with the hiring of Christopher D. Sliva to the newly-created position of Chief Operating Officer of its Bay Valley Foods operating unit and Senior Vice President of TreeHouse Foods. Sliva, 49, joins the company from Dean Foods where was Chief Commercial Officer of Fresh Dairy Direct-Morningstar.  In his new role at TreeHouse, Sliva will work closely with Bay Valley Food president Harry J. Walsh and report directly to Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer Sam K. Reed. He will be based at corporate headquarters in Oak Brook, Illinois. 
"The rapid growth and increased complexity of our company requires a new alignment of our executive leadership," Reed said. "Chris Sliva is highly qualified for the COO role. For the past six years, he has been a key member of the Executive Leadership Team of Dean Foods, the parent from which TreeHouse Foods was spun off in 2005." Prior to being named Chief Commercial Officer for Fresh Dairy Direct-Morningstar in 2010, Sliva was Chief Customer Officer for Dean's White Wave Foods division and President and Chief Operating Officer for the Morningstar division. His successful career in consumer packaged goods also includes positions at Eastman Kodak, Fort James Corporation and Procter & Gamble.  Sliva holds a bachelor's degree in Business Administration from Washington University in St. Louis.   
About TreeHouse Foods 
Formed in 2005, TreeHouse is a food manufacturer servicing primarily the retail grocery and foodservice channels. Its 15 major product lines include non-dairy powdered creamer; canned soup, refrigerated and shelf stable salad dressings, dips and sauces; powdered drink mixes; instant oatmeal and hot cereals; macaroni and cheese, skillet dinners and other value-added side dishes and salads; salsa and Mexican sauces; jams and pie fillings under the E.D. Smith brand name; pickles and related products; and other food products including aseptic sauces, and liquid non-dairy creamer. TreeHouse believes it is the largest manufacturer of pickles and non-dairy powdered creamer in the United States and the largest manufacturer of private label salad dressings, powdered drink mixes and instant hot cereals in the United States and Canada based on sales volume.  TreeHouse's annual sales are in excess of $2 billion. The company has 19 manufacturing plants and more than 4000 employees. 



